This paper focuses on fairness in machine learning, specifically in the context of healthcare. The use of neural networks and analysis of Pareto frontiers suggest a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), while the healthcare domain suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions predicting ICU patient mortality and classifying skin lesions from images, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and computer-based medical systems (cs.CR).
